# Space Trader Engine: Data Guide & Templates #

This document outlines the data structures required to build out the universe, economy, and narrative of the Space Trader engine. 

---

## 1. Encounters & Dialogues (`interactions`)
This is the narrative engine. Encounters are stored in the `interactions` object. Every encounter requires a `"start"` node to function.

```javascript
    "Template Character Name": {
        // --- OPTIONAL ROOT SETTINGS ---
        image: "portrait003.png",       // Portrait image in the assets folder
        requiresFlag: "heard_rumor",    // Character WON'T appear unless player has this flag
        hidesOnFlag: "mission_done",    // Character DISAPPEARS permanently once this flag is true
        
        // --- DIALOGUE TREE ---
        dialogue: {
            "start": {
                // You can use <br> for line breaks and <i> for italics
                text: "The room is dark.<br><br><i>\"Who goes there?\"</i>",
                options: [
                    // 1. A basic dialogue option leading to another node
                    { text: "Just a traveler.", nextNode: "ask_questions" },
                    
                    // 2. An option that ONLY appears if the player has a specific flag
                    { text: "Frank sent me.", nextNode: "secret_stash", requiresFlag: "knows_frank" },
                    
                    // 3. An option that HIDES once the player knows the information
                    { text: "What is this place?", nextNode: "lore_dump", hidesOnFlag: "knows_lore" },
                    
                    // 4. A transaction option (Cost) - Engine disables button if player can't afford it
                    { text: "Buy the map.", nextNode: "bought_map", credits: -50 },
                    
                    // 5. A transaction option (Reward)
                    { text: "Here is your package.", nextNode: "reward", credits: +200 },
                    
                    // 6. An option that alters the game state (Giving/Taking Flags)
                    { text: "I'll do the job.", nextNode: "leave", setFlag: "active_job", clearFlag: "looking_for_work" },

                    // 7. The special LEAVE command (Closes the encounter UI)
                    { text: "Goodbye. [Leave]", nextNode: "leave" }
                ]
            },
            
            // ... Next nodes go here, following the exact same structure as "start"
            "ask_questions": {
                text: "<i>\"Keep moving. We don't like strangers.\"</i>",
                options: [
                    { text: "[Leave]", nextNode: "leave" }
                ]
            }
        }
    },


##2. Galaxy Map & Stations (galaxy)
This array defines the physical map. It contains System objects, which in turn contain POI (Point of Interest) objects.

{ 
        id: 99,                     // Must be unique
        name: "Template System",    // Display name on the map
        x: 500, y: 500,             // Coordinates for the map canvas
        pois: [
            { 
                // --- STANDARD STATION ---
                name: "Template Hub", 
                type: "Trade Hub",    // Must match a type in stationTypes
                description: "A bustling center of commerce.", 
                image: "custom_station.png", // Optional: overrides default station image
            },
            { 
                // --- OUTPOST / DERELICT (No Market) ---
                name: "Abandoned Relay", 
                type: "Outpost",      // Outposts have no BUY/SELL buttons
                description: "It's completely dark.",
                
                // Adding characters to the station menu:
                encounters: ["Template Character Name", "Shady Bartender"], 
                
                // Hiding the ENTIRE station from the local menu based on state:
                requiresFlag: "has_coordinates", 
                hidesOnFlag: "relay_destroyed"
            }
        ] 
    },

##3. Station Economies (stationTypes)
This object dictates what markets buy and sell.

produces: An Array [] of items the station SELLS to the player.

consumes: An Object {} of items the station BUYS from the player, mapped to a demand multiplier.

"Template Factory Type": {
        defaultImage: "factory.png", // Used if the POI doesn't specify an image
        
        // Items it SELLS (Sold to player at a 20% discount from base price)
        produces: ["Machine Parts", "Microchips"],
        
        // Items it BUYS (Demand multipliers: High = +40%, Average = +20%, Low = +5%, TradeHub = +5%)
        consumes: { 
            "Copper Bars": "High", 
            "Iron Bars": "Average", 
            "Packaged Food": "Low" 
        }
    },

##4. Commodities (commodities)
This object sets the baseline economic rules for the randomizer. Every item in the game must be listed here for the market engine to function.

"Template Item": { 
        basePrice: 100, // The baseline "average" value
        min: 60,        // The absolute cheapest it can ever get during random fluctuations
        max: 150        // The absolute most expensive it can ever get
    },
